    "causal_summary": "Code graph operations have no doctor surface. When the index goes stale or bloats with `node_modules/`, `dist/`, generated artifacts, etc., users have to manually inspect `code_graph_status`, edit scanner config blind, run `code_graph_scan`, and spot-check queries. There is no command that walks them through diagnosis-first remediation with the same safety guarantees `/doctor:skill-advisor` provides (canonical-path validator, per-run rollback, dry-run preview, build-status branching).",
